cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of referring image segmentation, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a cross-modal self-attention module that captures long-range dependencies between linguistic and visual features, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a gated multi-level fusion module, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. Finally, the paper validates the proposed approach on four evaluation datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
